# ── supernova-competitor-ads — the rulebook ────────────────────────────────
# Git holds the small, precious text (scripts, master CSVs with every R2 link,
# inputs, logs, analysis). Heavy media lives in R2 and is pulled on demand with
# tools/rehydrate.py. This file controls only what is SHARED — it never deletes
# or blocks your local files.

# Secrets — never commit
**/.env
**/.env.*
!**/.env.template

# Heavy media — lives in R2, pulled on demand. Never commit.
**/videos/
**/images/

# Step 4 working files: exclude the HEAVY stuff, but KEEP every link record
# (the *.json sidecars, especially r2_urls.json) so all generated links stay in git.
**/step4_workspace/.gemini_uploads/
**/step4_workspace/batches/
**/step4_workspace/frames/
**/step4_workspace/logs/
**/step4_workspace/run_logs/
**/step4_workspace/docs/
**/step4_workspace/images/**/*.jpg
**/step4_workspace/images/**/*.jpeg
**/step4_workspace/images/**/*.png
# (everything else under step4_workspace — i.e. the .json link + analysis sidecars,
#  incl. scenes/*.json and images/<id>/r2_urls.json — is KEPT)

# Built Word docs and spreadsheet lock files — the docs live in R2 (links in master).
**/*.docx
**/~$*
**/.~lock.*

# Old manual backups — git history replaces these
**/*.bak
**/*.bak.*
**/*.pre-*
**/*.savedcopy
**/*.WRONG-SCHEMA-DO-NOT-RUN.csv

# Python / OS cruft
**/__pycache__/
**/*.pyc
**/.DS_Store

# Local scratch
**/.part
**/*.part
